Companion (bottom-screen spell buying): extend the open-signal patch to stream the session (NPC
name, player gold, purchasable+known spells with school + cost + known flag) and add extern "C"
control bridges (companionBuySpell / companionSpellBuyingCancel) driven from drainCompanionCommands,
mirroring companion-repair-export.patch. Unlike the native list, the export INCLUDES already-known
spells (known=1) so the overlay can grey them. companionExportOpen() runs at the end of setPtr, so a
purchase (companionBuySpellByIndex -> setPtr) re-exports with the bought spell now known and gold
updated; the ordinal index is stable because a purchase only flips a spell's known flag. COMPANION_
SPELLBUYING_CLOSED is emitted from every close path (onClose real-close, exit() for B/Escape, the
cancel bridge, onReferenceUnavailable) since the window is DS-hidden. Prices/school via
getBarterOffer/getSpellSchool (native-only). Added July 2026.

